spotted skink
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a skink distinguished by white or green black-edged flecks on its back and tail.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Oligosoma lineoocellatum</i> aka Mackenzie skink.  There is a subspecies known as Spotted skink "Mackenzie Basin" <i>Oligosoma aff. lineoocellatum "Mackenzie Basin"</i>
