Quote: Almost half of New Zealand's reptiles are threatened or endangered. It is now illegal to handle or keep in captivity any native lizard without a permit from the Department of Conservation. Some, such as the spotted skink (<i>Oligosoma lineoocellatum</i>), are still widespread, although their numbers are probably dwindling.
