Quote: <b>Spotted skink</b>: Oligosoma lineoocellatum, 111mm in length from snout to vent (minus tail).  It is much bigger than the common skink which is 73mm.  The king of the lizards in Ponatahi Lizard Sanctuary on Tim Hewitt's farm, he says he first saw them in the 1960s in their hundreds, but now they're rare.
